- Calling extern-C function with wrong argument number crash hrc

    extern ("C") {
      void exit(int retv);
    }


    def foo()
      exit()


- macros with empty replacement list are not registered?

    def macro assert {
      { assert(?expr:expr) } -> { }
    }

    def foo()
      assert(1 == 1)
      0


- functions from one compile units are not extern declared in another
  compile unit.